// Regression: a method declared with no receiver parameter at all (neither
// `&this`, `&mut this`, nor plain `this`) on a class with an owned field
// used to have its implicit `this` treated as an ordinary owned parameter,
// auto-dropped (destroying the object) at the end of the method body. Any
// further use of the object after such a call would then read freed
// memory. The implicit receiver now defaults to borrowed, so the object
// survives repeated calls and further field access.

import @firescript/std.io.println;

class Box {
    label: string;

    fn Box(&mut this, label: string) {
        this.label = label;
    }

    fn describe() -> string {
        return this.label;
    }
}

b: Box = new Box("first");
println(b.describe());
println(b.describe());
println(b.label);

/* EXPECT
first
first
first
*/
